history.content: This semester 61C and 188 seems to be a pretty popular combo, and it's a good balance in terms of workload! I'm personally taking these two with 2 more techs this semester.

children.subject: Taken all of these. IMO 188 was definitely the most fun, but that’s because I find AI super cool and interesting. I took 61C and 170 last fall. If you’d like explain how a computer really works take 61C. If you want some more software dev skills (eg for internship interviews next fall) take 170: I literally copied down the min edit distance algorithm we learned in class for an important coding challenge.

history.content:
I've taken 61A, 61B and 70 and am trying to decide what to take next Fall. 

Options are 61C, 170 and 188. I want to take the most fun out of these next sem (which seems like 188), but don't know if that makes sense given that I've only done 61AB and 70 till now. What do yall think? :)
